  "screenshot": "2026-07-06T14-53-20.png",
  "logTail": [
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "You open your eyes. Straw beneath you, the smell of wet rice, a low roof you do not know. A cold spring — the ninth year of An'ei — though the year is as lost to you as your name.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"You're awake.\" Sōan the physician sits back on his heels. \"No kami carried you off, whatever the village wants to believe. A flood took you, and a blow to the head took the rest. Bodies forget. Given work and rice, they also mend.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Sōan"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "You take stock of yourself: bruised, hollow, half-starved — but breathing.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "Rice lies scattered across the Kurosawa grain-store floor. Spilled stores are waste — and clearing waste is a kind of work, if you set your hands to it.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"How do I get my strength back?\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "You"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"Rest, rice, and work — in that order at first, then all at once. The body remembers labour before the mind remembers anything. The wits come back last; don't force them.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Sōan"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"There was a road. Grey rain. A name I can't hold. Is that the fever?\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "You"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"That is the blow talking, not a ghost. It will fade — or it won't. Don't let the old women make a haunting of it.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Sōan"
    },
    {
      "channel": "milestone",
      "text": "Perk unlocked — A Waking Fragment: A half-caught omen that bends fortune your way, though your step is slower to answer. (+1 LUCK / −1 AGI)",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "Something surfaces and is gone — a porter's knot, a road in grey rain, a name you cannot keep hold of.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"A porter's knot. My hands know this much.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "You"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "Your fingers move before you decide to — a labourer's memory, still in the muscle.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "milestone",
      "text": "Perk unlocked — The Porter's Hands: Hands that remember the work before the head does. (+1 STR / −1 LUCK)",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "On your feet, then. I am Genemon, steward of this house, and I keep the little it has left to keep. You'll not remember any of it, so hear it plain: the Kurosawa are samurai still — on the lord's rolls, if nowhere in the granary.",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Genemon"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"What work is there?\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "You"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"Rice to rake, a paddy to tend, a storehouse standing half-empty. Honest labour and no shortage of it. Earn your keep and there's a dry corner and a bowl in it — that's the whole of what I can promise.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Genemon"
    }
  ],
  "save": ""
}